		<div id="welcome">

			<h4>*ABOUT STAGE 1</h4>
			Each or any of the <i>Terms, Concept or Specific Objects</i>[words] presented in Stage 1 may invoke personal feelings, spark a particular philosophical interest, connect with you on spiritual level, all three or none at all. Based on your understanding of the words, it’s up to you to reflect on your life’s experience and make selections using our custom graphic interface.<a style="font-weight:700;" href="#" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#definition" data-whatever="UI Example"> See Example</a>
			<br /><br />
			<img src="img/s1Img.jpg" style="float:left; margin:0 20px 15px 0;"/>
			<div>
				<strong>Select up to four categories for any given word</strong><br />
				<ul class="about">
					<li>Man's View of Himself (Himself/Herself)</li>
					<li>Man's Connections with Other than Himself</li>
					<li>Man's View of the World</li>
					<li>Man's Physical Activities</li>
				</ul>
				<strong>The word "Man" means the <i>universal man</i> of which you are an example. <br />As such, you may:</strong><br />
            	<ul class="about">
					<li>Personalize any or all words to yourself</li>
					<li>Think of others exclusively</li>
					<li>Think of yourself and others together</li>
            	</ul>
				<strong>Opinion</strong><br />
			<ul class="about">
				<li><a style="font-weight:700;" href="#" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#definition" data-whatever="Spiritual">Spiritual</a> -- incorruptible | intangible | genuine and essential</li>
				<li><a style="font-weight:700;" href="#" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#definition" data-whatever="Material">Material</a> -- can be physical, intellectual or mixed | is composed of non-essential parts | can be degraded</li>
				<li><a style="font-weight:700;" href="#" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#definition" data-whatever="Material Spiritual Converging">Spiritual & Material Converging</a> -- unified in a way where, together, it's more than its seperate parts.</li>
				<!--Hypothetical 4: You eat <strong>bread</strong> all the time but never gave it much thought. One day you read how the invention of <strong>bread</strong> was quintessential in man's ability to thrive today.-->
			</ul>
			
			</div><br />
			
			<div id="howto-msg">Continue on to<a href="https://ybigh.herokuapp.com/n-stage1"> Stage 1</a></div>
		 	
		</div>

  	<!-- definitions Modal -->
  <div class="modal fade" id="definition" role="dialog">
    <div class="modal-dialog"> 
      <!-- Modal content-->
      <div class="modal-content">
        <div class="modal-header">
          <h4 class="modal-title"></h4>
        </div>
        <div class="modal-body">
        </div>
        <div class="modal-footer">
          <button type="button" class="btn btn-default" data-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
        </div>
      </div>
      
    </div>
  </div>
	<script type="text/javascript" src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/jquery/3.3.1/jquery.min.js"></script>
  	<script type="text/javascript" src="libs/boostrap4/js/bootstrap.min.js"></script>

  	<script type="text/javascript">

  	let content = {
  		Material_Spiritual_Converging: "The spiritual realm adds depth and meaning to the material object while the "+ "material allows expression of the spiritual realm by being its conduit or physical embodiment. A material-spiritual convergence is greater than its individual separate parts.<br /><br /> Like steel reinforcing "+ "concrete. The steel gives flexibility to the concrete and the concrete gives strength to the steel.<br /><br /><strong>Examples of Spiritual & Material Converging</strong>: "+
        "<br />1) You're stranded out at sea and all you have to drink is your own<strong> Urine</strong>. It saves your life."+ 
        "<br />2) You hear about an out-of-control <strong>truck</strong> killing 5 people on a busy <strong>sidewalk</strong>."+
        "<br />3) The <strong>county fair</strong> always held a special place in your heart",
  		Spiritual: "<ul>"+
          	"<li><strong>incorruptible</strong>: beyond reproach or needs no justification -- holy text, animal instict, or evil itself, as examples</li>"+
              "<li><strong>intangible</strong>: can't be held or touched. Has no physical presence</li>"+
          	"<li><strong>genuine</strong>: corroborates with what the mind knows it should be and what the thing actually is -- actual gold vs. fools gold</li>"+ 
          	"<li><strong>essential</strong>: complete in a way where it's impossible to think of it differently -- the essence of a circle is its round, uniform shape. Try imagining a square circle if you can</li><br /><strong>Summary:</strong> The spiritual realm constitutes things we can feel, believe, or know but not [always] understand in their entirety. "+
           "</ul>",
        Material: "<ul>"+
          	"<li><strong>composed of non-essential parts</strong>: remove its parts and it still exists as that thing -- removing, for example, one act of A Play doesn't make it not A Play</li>"+
          	"<li><strong>degradable</strong>: can be ruined or destroyed by a person or over time -- steel on a car eventually corrodes, a Xerox machine can be crushed using a bat, and birthdays become a drag as you grow older</li>"+
            "<li><strong>can be physical, intellectual or mixed</strong>: has form and exists in space and/or time -- String Theory is a purely intellectual material object. It has many parts and is susceptible to degradation if it can't be proven. A Play is a mixed material object. While the notion of 'A Play' is intellectual, many of its parts--people & props--are physical.<br />The existance of 'Plays' suffers from degradation due to competing forms of entertainment such as TV and movies. </li>"+
            "<br /><strong>Summary:</strong> Material objects are [most] things we can create, imagine, or discover.</ul>",
        UI_Example: "<img src='img/s1Img1.jpg' style='margin:10px;'/>"

  	}
  		$('#definition').on('show.bs.modal', function (event) {
  			var button = $(event.relatedTarget); // Button that triggered the modal
  			var recipient = button.data('whatever'); // Extract info from data-* attributes
  			var key = recipient.replace(/ /g, "_");
  			var gcontent = content[key];
  			var modal = $(this);
  			modal.find('.modal-title').text(recipient);
  			$('.modal-body').empty();
  			modal.find('.modal-body').append(gcontent);
		})

  	</script>
	</body>
</html>
